			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">At level 47, I'm currently hunting Gornit w/o KEI. The great part about Gornit is not only does he drop lots of coin, but also an item (whether it's good to loot or not isn't important in this). Now, you can wait to loot it (or if it's a Pirate Earring, not loot it at all!), and time his spawns by his corpse decay rate. When it reaches about 2 mins 5 seconds, he will spawn again. On Kane Bayle, it seems no one even knows this guy exists, and I can make two trips per day on him. So far, I've made about 4 trips (3 trips and 2 half trips, only filled bags halfway), and I've made a little over 2.5k on him. This does take a while, each camp seems to be somewhere around 2 1/2 hours, but it's worth it. Bring a book and catch up on some reading while you're there, it's what I do... also, since it takes him 6 minutes to spawn, and you'll be fm by the time he spawns again (fm really isn't req'd), you can spend this time working on skills you need to build up. For me, it's Alt and Abj, but whatever skill you aren't good in.
<br />

<br />
I have 3 summoned bags full, one with only food & water, one sewing kit, and a dusty ransacker's pack that has 6 items in it already, room for two more. It might be easier if you have some str gear to bring (lots of int gear not req'd), and Gift of Xev. I have 70 str, I get up to about 175/70 before I leave, and I'm saving up for a drog.
<br />

<br />
Oh, pull with Malaise (or whatever resist debuff you prefer), start a nuke at 90 pct (adjusted downward for stronger ones than Shock of Swords), and one at 30 pct of his health, the first to make sure he doesn't kill your pet before you finish him off (stronger pets may be able to solo him), and the second to make sure he doesn't run. I have little problem with aggro when using air unless I get too close.
<br />

<br />
Though likely, Gornit wouldn't be the best choice for cash at this level, it ain't bad if you've got nothing else to do.<br />_________________<br />Oldest joke in the world:
<br />
Let there be light!
<br />
Second oldest joke:
<br />
Life.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
