				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This morning, I made the run to Dulak's Harbor to check it out. I arrived at about 9:00 PST, set up on Lady Dirulia, summoned the level 51 earth pet, cast BO3 & SoL on him, & began pulling. I pulled Dirulia crewmen & cannoneers until about 10:24 PST, when I had to go run a RL errand.
<br />

<br />
In that time, I got:
<br />

<br />
1 Blue Diamond
<br />
2 research words
<br />
1 Bronze Medallion of Service
<br />
1 Essence of Mar
<br />

<br />
& about 79 plat in total cash, to go with 3.5 blue bubbles of XP.
<br />

<br />
It was safe & easy, but, apparently, either the drop rates in this zone have been nerfed dramatically, or I simply got very unlucky. In any event, I'm suspicious that maybe Nadox elementals are better at 52nd level, but that's based solely on having killed ONE measly Scorn Elemental at the zone line; I got nearly 9 plat in cash from it, plus a thing of enchanted ash that sold to vendors for another 9.5 plat, plus nearly 2 full blue ticks of XP. That is SERIOUS reward for a mob that was just a little harder to kill than a Dulak's boat crewman, & Nadox is slightly "easier" to get to as well, given that you don't have to run quite as far through the mob-infested Gunthak tunnels.<br />_________________<br />Benbow Bookbinder, 58 Elementalist, Veeshan
<br />
Mark of the Black Frog
<br />
So many books, so little time!
<br />
