			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm shooting myself in the foot here, but oh well.
<br />

<br />
Try the shadow island in the Twilight sea.  It is the island E-SE of the elemental island with transon's castle on it.  If you are at the gates of the castle, run straight east, and its the first island there.
<br />

<br />
The mobs there top out at lvl 40, but the idea here is that they all drop Swirling Shadows pretty frequently.  At 64 (any 60+) you can clear the island in 10-15 minutes, and get anywhere from 12-18 shadows per cycle.
<br />

<br />
They don't sell to vendors, but they DO sell to players pretty well.  On my server, they are currently going for 40PP each, but they used to go for 75PP each.  The reason that they go for so much is that they can be a pain to farm, and they are for shadowscream armour, which is one of the few ways to get to 250 in blacksmithing.
<br />

<br />
The re-pop is somewhere between 20 minutes and half an hour.  So you can't really stay there once you get higher because of the re-pop time, but if you got exp from this in yer 40s, it might even out, but would be a dangerous spot to hunt because virtually all of them wander.  But if you are lfg sometime, just swing by twilight via fungus grove, harvest a cycle's worth, and dump them on your vendor mule.  Then when you go to work during the day, set up your vendor, and you should have nearly 1k per cycle.
<br />

<br />
The other bonus here are the named.  Some of them are "a groaning shadow" and other weird names.  Usually, it is lesser and greater shadows.  But anything with a different name will either drop an item, or a piece for the twilight armour quests.  The regular weapons they carry suck, and i don't even bother looting them (spiny), but these drops can sometimes be valuable in the bazaar, and there is usually 0-4 named per island cycle.
<br />

<br />
Try it out.  Its one place for money, but usuall only "idleing" while waiting for other things.<br />_________________<br />Eriol Telcontar
<br />
Arch Convoker - Master of the Orb
<br />
The Death Squad
<br />
The Tribunal</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
